reviews.reviewTitle: Great Night Stand For Low Bed
reviews.reviewText: When searching for a nightstand, I needed one fairly low to the ground as my bed was not the highest. I stumbled across this nightstand, and it checked off all my boxes. Easy to assemble, Nice and sturdy, Nice accessories (USB and Plug at the top of stand), and also has a convenient self and drawer. Please note that if you have a high bed, then this product may not be for you; look at the dimensions before purchasing. Evidently, this product has been doing its job! 5 Stars!!

I really like this side table. I am using it as a beside table, it is perfect for plugging in a lamp and twp chargers. Using it the first couple times it gave a faint burnt plastic smell and the power bar overheated, but as with any power bar, you should not overload it with several plugs as I did (one lamp and two devices that needed a full charge). Use this as you should any power bar and only use a couple appliances at once. There has been no burning plastic smell or overheating since.The adjustable feet are very useful for balancing the table on either an uneven surface or on two different surfaces. The shelf at the bottom is a nice space for any small things you need to store.Assembling it was a bit cumbersome. I am pretty handy at putting things together, but it was quite a process. It took a couple hours to put together. The instructions are very detailed and leave no question what it is you need to do. Some of the holes were drilled too small, so I had to find a way to either enlarge the hole or to skip that part altogether. I managed to place every screw and dowel with the exception of one screw on either side of the drawer because these holes were just too tight. The drawer is still remarkably sturdy for missing two screws.

reviews.reviewTitle: The white smooth finish very nice and well designed.
